rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Value type collecting data on an object's apparent dimensions. These are the measurements of the major and minor axes of the object.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Scheinbare Dimension
Apparent Dimension
Dimensi??n aparente
Dimension apparente

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.apparent_dimension value type to the major axis of the object. The major axis is the longest diameter of an ellipse.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Major Axis

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.apparent_dimension value type to the minor axis of the object, which is the longest line segment perpendicular to the major axis
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Minor Axis

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Value Type collecting the data on an object's apparent mass. It includes the object's mass and its uncertainty.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Scheinbare Masse
Apparent Mass
Masa aparente
Masse apparente

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.apparent_mass value type to the mass of an object in solar mass units.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mass

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.apparent_mass value type to the uncertainty of the mass calculation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Uncertainty

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all asterisms. These are the patterns of stars that are recognized as a unit. They include parts of constellations or may be a pattern of stars from more than one constellation. See also mso:astronomy.constellation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Asterism
Asterismo
Ast??risme
Asterism

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.asterism to its component mso:astronomy.celestial_objects. These are the principal celestial objects, like stars or nebulae that appear to form the pattern. Typically, they form the vertices or end points of the imaginary lines between the stars that form the shape.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Celestial Object

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.asterism to the mso:astronomy.constellation(s) that this asterism appears in or overlaps.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Constellations

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of asteroids. Asteroids are the minor planets, especially those found in the inner Solar System.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Asteroid
Asteroid
Asteroide
Ast??roide
Kisbolyg??

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.asteroid to the mso:astronomy.asteroid_group of which the asteroid is a part.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Asteroid Group

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:mso:astronomy.asteroid to its mso:astronomy.asteroid_spectral_type, which is a means of classify asteroids by various characteristics.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Spectral Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:astronomy.asteroid to the mso:astronomy.asteroid_family of which it is a part.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Member of Family

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary collection representing the collection of all asteroid families. These are the groups of asteroids that share orbital elements, like mso:astronomy.asteroid_groups, but are further related because they are believed to be fragments of an asteroid collision.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Asteroid Family
Asteroide de la familia
Asteroid famille

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.asteroid_family to its member mso:astronomy.asteroids.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Asteroid Family Member

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:asteroid_family to the mso:astronomy.asteroid that the family is named for or that was the first of the family discovered.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Founding Asteroid Family Member

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all asteroid groups. These are the groups of mso:astronomy.asteroids that share common orbital elements, but unlike mso:astronomy.asteroid_familys, these asteroids are unrelated in any other way.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Asteroid Group

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.asteroid_group to the mso:astronomy.asteroid, that is the largest member or the member the group is named for.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Asteroid Group Founding Member

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all asteroid spectral types. These are the groupings of asteroids by shared characteristics, including spectral shape, color, and sometimes albedo.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Asteroid Spectral Type
Type spectral d'ast??ro??de

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:astronomy.asteroid_spectral_type to the mso:astronomy.asteroids assigned this type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Asteroids of this Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all astronomers. These are the people that study celestial bodies.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Astronom
Astronomer
Astr??nomo
Astronome

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:astronomy.astronomer to the mso:astronomy.astronomical_discovery relationship, which collects the data on a discovery the astronomer made.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Discovered

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all astronomical discoveries. These are previously unknown celestial objects or objects of celestial origin, e.g. a meteorite on the Earth's surface, that are observed and named by an astronomer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Astronomical Discovery
Descubrimiento astron??mico

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.astronomical_discovery to the mso:astronomy.astronomer(s) that made the discovery.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Discoverer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.astronomical_discovery to the date the discovery was made.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Discovery Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.astronomical_discovery to the mso:astronomy.astronomical_survey_project_organization associated with the discovery. This could be the organization that sponsored the research, or employs the astronomers that made the discovery, or is related to the discovery in some other manner.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Discovery Organization

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.astronomical_discovery to the mso:astronomy.astronomical_observatory where the discovery was made.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Discovery Site

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.astronomical_discovery to the mso:astronomy.astronomical_discovery_technique that was used to make the discovery.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Discovery Technique

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.astronomical_discovery to the status of the discovery. Examples include confirmed, published, or announced.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Status

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all statuses of astronomy.discoveries.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Astronomical Discovery Status
Le statut de d??couverte astronomique

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all methods of making astronomy discoveries.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Astronomical Discovery Technique
Technique de d??couverte astronomique

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a standard descriptor for a method of astronomical discovery to a particular discovery made by the method.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Astronomical Discoveries

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all astronomical observatories. These are the locations for observing and studying celestial objects.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Astronomical Observatory
Observatorio Astron??mico
Observatoire astronomique

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:astronomy.astronomical_observatory to the mso:astronomy.astronomical_discoveries made at the observatory.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: discoveries

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:astronomy.astronomical_observatory to the mso:astronomy.telescope(s) that are a part of the observatory.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Telescope

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all astronomy organizations. These are the organizations dedicated to conducting and sponsoring research of celestial objects.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Astronomical Organization

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.astronomical_survey_project_organization to the mso:astronomy.astronomical_observatory associated with the organization.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Observatory

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:astronomy.astronomical_survey_project_organization to the mso:astronomy.astronomical_discoveries associated with the organization.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Celestial Objects Discovered

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all celestial objects. These are the the naturally occurring physical entities, associations, or structures that current science has demonstrated to exist in the observable universe.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Celestial Object
Objeto celeste
Objet c??leste

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The measure of an object's brightness derived from an adjusted apparent magnitude if the object is observed at a fixed distance of 1 AU (10 parsecs) with no appreciable intervening dust or other light absorbing material.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Absolute Magnitude

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.celestial_object to its albedo, which is the diffuse reflectivity of its surface.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Albedo

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.celestial_object to its axial tilt. The axial tilt is the angle between the object's rotational axis and its orbital axis.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Axial Tilt

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.celestial_object to its apparent age in million of light years.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Age

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.celestial_object to its mso:astronomy.celestial_object_category, e.g., galaxy, nebula, star, asteroid, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a celestial object to information about the distance between the celestial object and other celestial objects.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Celestial Object Distance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The color index is a simple numerical expression that determines the color of an object, which in the case of a star gives its temperature. To measure the index, one observes the magnitude of an object successively through two different filters, such as U and B, or B and V, where U is sensitive to ultraviolet rays, B is sensitive to blue light, and V is sensitive to visible (green-yellow) light.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Color Index

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.celestial_object to its best approximated distance from the earth in parsecs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Distance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:atronomy.celestial_object to its declination, abbrev. dec or ??. This is one of the two coordinates of the equatorial coordinate system and is comparable to geographic latitude, but projected onto the celestial sphere. Declination is measured in degrees north and south of the celestial equator. Points north of the celestial equator have positive declinations, while those to the south have negative declinations.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Declination

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.celestial_object to its circumference at its equator, as measured in kilometers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Equatorial Circumference

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.celestial_object to its escape velocity as measured in meters per second. This is the speed objects in the body's gravitational field need to break free from the gravitational field. Technically, this is the speed at which the kinetic energy plus the gravitational potential energy of an object is zero.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Escape Velocity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.celestial_object to its surface gravity, g. This is the gravitational acceleration experienced at the object's surface. It is measured in is measured in units of acceleration.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Surface Gravity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.celestial_object to its Hipparcos Catalog number. This catalog contains 118,218 stars that were observed by the European Space Agency's Hipparcos Satellite from late 1989 to 1993. The Hipparcos Catalog Data is purely based on observations performed in space, except for the global orientation of its reference frame which was adjusted to the existing system by a variety of mainly ground-based techniques.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hipparcos Catalog Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:atronomy.celestial_object to its apparent magnitude, the measurement of its brightness as seen by an observer on Earth, which is normalized to the value absent any atmosphere. The brighter the object, the lower the value. For example, the Sun has an apparent magnitude of -26.74.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Magnitude

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.celestial_object to its mass in kg.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mass

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.celestial_object to its mean density. This is the volumetric mass density of the substances making up the object.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mean Density

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.celestial_object to its mean radius. This is the mean distance from the center of the object to its surface.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mean Radius

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a celestial object to the quadrant where the celestial object is located. For locating celestial objects, the celestial sphere is divided into four southern and four northern quadrants, where the center of the sphere is the Sun.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Quadrant

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.celestial_object to the mso:astronomy.red_shift value type that holds the data for the object's red shift. This is the apparent velocity in kilometers of the object traveling away (or towards) the observing location, usually the Earth.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Red Shift

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.celestial_objec to its right ascension. This is the celestial equivalent of terrestrial longitude. Both right ascension and longitude measure an angle that increases toward the east as measured from a zero point on an equator. For longitude, the zero point is the Prime Meridian on the geographic equator; for right ascension, the zero point is known as the first point of Aries, which is the place in the sky where the Sun crosses the celestial equator at the March equinox.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Right Ascension

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.celestial_object to its rotation period. This is the time it takes to complete one revolution around its axis of rotation. This is different from the object's solar day, which includes an extra fractional rotation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sidereal Rotation Period

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a celestial object to the solid angle that the object subtends in the sky, measured in square degrees.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Solid Angle

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.celestial_object to its surface area. This is the total area that the surface of an object occupies.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Surface Area

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a celestial object to the entity, e.g. from mythology, that the object represents. For example, the constellation Orion represents the mythological huntsman Orion.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Symbolism

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.celestial_object to the average temperature for the object.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Average Temperature

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.celestial_object to its volume in cubic km.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Volume

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Value type collecting the data on the age of a celestial age.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Celestial Object Age
??ge d'objet c??leste

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.celestial_object_age value type to the apparent age in millions of years.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Age

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.celestial_object_age value type to the estimated error associated with the age of the object.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Uncertainty

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all celestial object categories. These are the groupings of objects that share similar characteristics.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Celestial Object Category
Cat??gorie d'objets c??lestes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:astronomy.celestial_object_category to the subtypes of the category. For example, a subcategory of giant star is red giant.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Subcategories
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use type.object.subtype instead. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:type.object.subtype]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.celestial_object_category to its super-category. For example, plutoids are a type of trans-neptunian object.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Subcategory of
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use type.object.supertype instead. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:type.object.supertype]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that stores information about the distance between two celestial objects.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Celestial Object Distance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the average distance between the two celestial objects. Note that two celestial objects can be at various distances from each other depending on the time, because they may be moving at different speeds, they may be in orbit, and these two factors may move them closer together or farther apart from time to time.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Average Distance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the celestial objects that have the given distance from each other.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Celestial Object

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the maximum distance between the two celestial objects. Note that two celestial objects can be at various distances from each other depending on the time, because they may be moving at different speeds, they may be in orbit, and these two factors may move them closer together or farther apart from time to time.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Distance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the minimum distance between the two celestial objects. Note that two celestial objects can be at various distances from each other depending on the time, because they may be moving at different speeds, they may be in orbit, and these two factors may move them closer together or farther apart from time to time.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Minimum Distance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all celestial objects that have been assigned a coordinate system to map the objects features.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Celestial Object with Coordinate System

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: such as areographic coordinates on Mars, selenographic coordinates on the Moon, and heliographic coordinates on the Sun
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Planetographic coordinate system

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all comets. These are the smaller, icy celestial objects that have a visible outer coma and tail.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Comet
Cometa
Com??te

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.comet to its mso:astronomy.comet_group.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Comet Group

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The Designation is the official alphanumeric identifier for the comet.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Designation
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Redundant with type.object.official_name. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\jcoop] Successor:[mso:type.object.official_name]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.comet to the date of the comet's last closest visit to the Earth's sun.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Last Perihelion

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:astronomy.comet to the mso:astronomy.meteor_shower the comet creates. The shower is caused by the vaporization of some of the comet's ice, which releases meteoroids.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Meteor Shower Spawned

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.comet to the date of the comet's next closet visit to the Earth's sun.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Next Perihelion (Predicted)

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all comet groups. These are the sets of comets that either travel together or were split from the same ancestor comet.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Comet Group
Cometa grupo
Comet Group

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:astronomy.comet_group to the mso:astronomy.comet that is a part of the group.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: comet

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all constellations. In modern astronomy, these are the celestial locations that are internationally recognized, usually grouped and defined by patterns of celestial objects like stars.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Constellation
Constelaci??n
Constellation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a constellation to the number of stars in the constellation that appear in either the Bayer or the Flamsteed designation of stars.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bayer Flamsteed Stars

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:astronomy.constellation to the mso:astronomy.constellation_bordering_relationship that contains data about the border between two constellations. Note that the virtual property definition on this property should be removed, and the expected type should be changed to astronomy.constellation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bordering Constellations

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a constellation to the brightest star in the constellation, as seen from earth.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Brightest Star

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a constellation to a family of which the constellation is a part. For example, the constellation Aries is part of the Zodiac constellation family.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Constellation Family

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:astronomy.constellation to the mso:astronomy.star that is part of the constellation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Contains

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.constellation to the mso:astronomy.galaxies that are observed within the constellation's location.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Galaxies

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a constellation to the number of main stars in the constellation. A main star is a star that can be recognized from earth.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Main Stars

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a constellation to the number of celestial objects in the constellation that have a Messier designation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Messier Objects

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.constellation to the mso:astronomy.meteor_shower(s) that originate in the constellation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Meteor Showers

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a constellation to the star in the constellation that is closest to earth.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nearest Star

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a constellation to the number of celestial objects in the constellation that are brighter than 3 apparent magnitudes. Apparent magnitude, abbreviated m, is a measure of the brightness of celestial objects as seen from earth.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Stars Brighter than 3 Apparent Magnitudes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a constellation to the number of stars with planets that are in the constellation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Stars with Planets

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a constellation to the number of celestial objects in the constellation that are within 10 parsecs of earth. Parsec is a measure of astronomical distance used for objects outside of the Solar System.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Stars within 10 Parsecs

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship collecting the data on the border between two mso:astronomy.constellations. Note: it is not clear that this data really needs to be contained in a relationship: if there is no other data that needs to be added to the entity, this should more properly be a property on mso:astronomy.constellation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Constellation Bordering Relationship
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: If the single property on this type is needed, it should be placed on astronomy.constellation or a broader term. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.constellation_bordering_relationship to the mso:astronomy.constellation(s) that share a border.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Constellations
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: If this property is needed, it should be placed on astronomy.constellation or a broader term. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A set of constellations having a common attribute. For example, the Zodiac is a family of 12 constellations.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Constellation Family

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of dwarf planets. These are the celestial objects that are the same size as a planet, but are neither a planet nor a moon or other natural satellite. This is not the same as a minor planet.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:dwarf_planet to the mso:astronomy.star_system in which it is located.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all extraterrestrial locations. These are the named locations found on objects other than the Earth. Note: further investigation on the instances of this type is needed before assigning an mso:geography.geographical_feature base_class to this type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Extraterrestrial Location

This property is different from mso:astronomy.extraterrestrial_location.contained_by, which is restricted to other mso:astronomy.extraterrestrial_locations, and not the larger mso:astronomy.celestial_object.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Celestial Object

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.extraterrestrial_location to its mso:astronomy.type_of_planetographic_feature.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Planetographic Feature Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all galaxy clusters. These are the large celestial structures of galaxies, hundreds to thousands of galaxies that are bound by gravity.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.galactic_cluster to the mso:astronomy.galactic_super_cluster of which the galaxy cluster is a part.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Supercluster

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:astronomy.galactic_cluster to the mso:astronomy.galactic_group of which the cluster is a part.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Galaxy Groups

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all galaxy filaments. These are the massive, thread-like cosmic structures that form the boundaries between large voids in the universe. They are made up of gravitationally bound galaxies, including superclusters.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Galactic Filament
Filaments galactiques

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:astronomy.galactic_filament to the mso:astronomy.galactic_super_cluster contained within the filament.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Superclusters

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all galaxy groups. These are the sets of galaxies with fewer than 50 members that are bound by gravity. For sets of more than 50 members, see also mso:astronomy.galactic_cluster. mso:astronomy.galactic_super_clusters are those objects that are made up of galaxy groups and clusters.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Galaxy Group
Gal??ctica grupo
Groupe Galactic

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.galactic_group to the mso:astronomy.galactic_cluster(s) found within the group.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:astronomy.galactic_group to the mso:astronomy.galaxy found within the group.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Galaxies

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship collecting the data the interaction between two galaxies. This includes the galaxies, the interaction type, its status, and the duration of this interaction.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Galactic Interaction
Gal??ctica interacci??n
Interaction galactique

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.galactic_interaction relationship to the length of time of the interaction.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Duration

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.galactic_interaction relationship to the mso:astronomy.galactic_interaction_status of the interaction.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Status

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.galactic_interaction to the mso:astronomy.galactic_interaction_type, like 'collision' or 'cannibalism'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Interaction Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:astronomy.galactic_interaction relationship to the mso:astronomy.galaxies participating in the interaction.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Galaxy

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.galactic_interaction with the time in millions of years when the interaction will or did take place. For interactions that took place in the past, use a negative value.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: When

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all interaction statuses for galaxies.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Galactic Interaction Status
Statut de l'interaction galactique

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all galaxy interaction types. These are the groupings of interactions that share common characteristics, which includes collision and cannibalism.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Galactic Interaction Type
Type d'interaction galactique

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.galactic_interaction_type to the mso:astronomy.galactic_interaction relationship that collects data on the galaxies that have this interaction type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Galaxies

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all galaxy shape types. These are the groupings of galaxies based on morphological similarities.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Galaxy Shape Type
Gal??ctica forma
Forme galactique

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a standard descriptor for a shape of galaxies, e.g. spiral galaxy, to a particular galaxy having this shape.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Galaxies
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The type astronomy.galaxy_classification_code has been deprecated. If a property relating glactic shape to galaxies having the shape is needed, then the expected type should be changed to astonomy.galaxy. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all superclusters. These are the immense cosmic structures made up of galaxy groups and galaxy clusters.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Galaxy Supercluster
Superamas galactique

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.galactic_super_cluster to its containing mso:astronomy.galactic_filament.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Galaxy Filament

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:astronomy.galactic_super_cluster to the mso:astronomy.galactic_cluster the supercluster contains.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Galaxy Clusters

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all galaxies. These are the gravitationally bound entities made up of stars, stellar remnants, gas, dust, other object, and dark matter.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Galaxy
Galaxia
Galaxie

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.galaxy to its mso:astronomy.apparent_mass, the value type collecting the mass and uncertainty for the object.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Apparent mass

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.galaxy to the mso:astronomy.constellations found within the galaxy.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Constellation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.galaxy to its mso:astronomy.apparent_dimensions, collecting the data on the galaxy's major and minor axes in Arc Min.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Apparent Dimension

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.galaxy to its containing mso:astronomy.galactic_group ie., Milky Way and Andromeda galaxies are part of the Local Galaxy Group.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Galaxy Group

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.galaxy to the mso:astronomy.galactic_interaction relationship collecting data about the galaxy's interactions with other galaxies, which can include colliding, cannibalism, and merging.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Interaction

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.galaxy to its mso:astronomy.galaxy_classification_code, which is a type of morphological classification.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Classification
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use media_common.cataloged_instance.number instead. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:media_common.cataloged_instance.number]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.galaxy to its mso:astronomy.number_of_stars, the value type collecting the data on the estimated number of stars in the galaxy and a margin of error.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Stars

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.galaxy to its mso:astronomy.satellite_galaxy. Please see also mso:astronomy.galaxy.galactic_interaction for other types of galaxy interactions.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Satellite Galaxies

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all galaxy classification codes. These are the classification groupings of galaxies based on appearance.

Code de classification Galaxy
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: Use media_common.cataloged_instance to record codes of galaxies and other astronomical discoveries. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:media_common.cataloged_instance]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.galaxy_classification_code to the mso:astronomy.galactic_shape of the galaxies in this code.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Galaxy Shape
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The type of this property has been deprecated. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:astronomy.galaxy_classification_code to the mso:astronomy.galaxies with this code.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Galaxies
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The type of this property has been deprecated. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all meteor showers. These are the recurring celestial events where a number of meteors can be observed from one general area in the sky.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Meteor Shower
Meteor Shower

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.meteor_shower to the mso:astronomy.meteor_shower_occurrence that is a given instance of the shower.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Radiant

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.meteor_shower to the mso:astronomy.comet that is the source of the meteor-producing debris.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Comet

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Value type representing the collection of all meteor shower occurrences, which is the period of time a given instance of meteor shower is observable.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.meteor_shower_occurrence to the date the maximum Zenithal Hourly Rate occurs.

M??t??orite

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Specimen Location

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.meteorite to its mso:astronomy.meteoric_composition.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all natural satellites. These are the celestial objects that orbit another due to gravitational pull.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Natural Satellite
Luna
Lune

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all near-earth objects. These are the celestial objects that come close to the earth. These object approach to the Sun, also called the perihelion, of less than 1.3 AU.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Near-Earth Object

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.near_earth_object to itsmso:astronomy.near_earth_object_classification, which are the groupings of such objects by shared characteristics.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Near-Earth Object Classification

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of near-earth object types. These are groupings of NEOs by characteristics. An example of this grouping is 'meteoroid'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Near-Earth Object Classification

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:astronomy.near_earth_object_classification to the mso:astronomy.near_earth_object(s) that are classified in this type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Near-Earth Objects

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all nebulae. These are the regions of interstellar dust and gas clouds that are usually responsible for forming stars.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nebula
Nebulosa
N??buleuse

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Value type collecting the data on the number of stars for a given entity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Stars
Nombre d'??toiles

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.number_of_stars to the estimated number of stars in the celestial object.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Stars

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.number_of_stars value type to the estimated error range for the given estimated stars.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Uncertainty

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all types of orbits. These are the groupings of orbits that shared common characteristics. For example, a heliocentric orbit has an orbit around a star.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Orbit Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:astronomy.orbit_type to the mso:astronomy.orbital_relationship(s) of this type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Orbiting Bodies of Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of orbital relationships. These entities collect the data on the orbits of objects. Note: this type's category should be changed from 'primary entity' to 'relationship'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Orbital Relationship
Orbital Relations

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.orbital_relationship to the orbiting object's furthest point from the orbited object.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Apoapsis

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.orbital_relationship to the argument of perihelion, which is one of the orbital elements used to specify the orbit of an object in space. Specifically, it is the angle between the orbit's periapsis (the point of closest approach to the central point) and the orbit's ascending node (the point where the body crosses the plane of reference from South to North).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Argument of Perihelion

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.orbital_relationship to the Julian date that is the reference point of the orbital datum.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Epoch

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.orbital_relationship to the angle of the orbit to the rotational plane of the object being orbited.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Inclination

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.orbital_relationship to the longitude of the ascending node. This is one of the orbital elements used to specify the orbit of an object in space. It is the angle from a reference direction, called the origin of longitude, to the direction of the ascending node, measured in a reference plane.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Longitude of Ascending Node

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.orbital_relationship to its mean anomaly, which is a parameter relating position and time for a body moving in a Kepler orbit.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mean Anomaly

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.orbital_relationship to the mean speed the orbiting object travels around the orbited object.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Average Orbital Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.orbital_relationship to the amount of deviation the orbit has from a perfect circle. A value of 0 is a circular orbit, values between 0 and 1 form an elliptical orbit, 1 is a parabolic escape orbit, and greater than 1 is a hyperbola.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Orbit Eccentricity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.orbital_relationship to the type of orbit between the given orbiting object and the orbited object.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Orbit Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.orbital_relationship to the orbiting objects order around the orbited object, if there is more than one. For example, Earth is the 3rd Planet in orbit around the Sun.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Orbital Order

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.orbital_relationship to the number of Earth days the orbiting object takes to complete one orbit.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Orbital Period

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:astronomy.orbital_relationship to the orbiting object. Note that the virtual property definition associated with this property needs to be removed, and the expected type of this property needs to change to mso:astronomy.celestial_object.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Orbited by

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.orbital_relationship to the object that is orbited. Note that when the base_class relationship between mso:astronomy.orbital_relationship and mso:astronomy.celestial_object is removed, this expected type will need to change to mso:astronomy.celestial_object.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Orbited Object

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.orbital_relationship to the periapsis of the orbiting bodies. This is the smallest distance that occurs on the orbit between the two bodies.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Periapsis

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.orbital_relationship to its semi-major axis. This is half the distance of an elliptical's major axis, the distance through the center and both foci, with ends at the widest points of the perimeter.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Semi-major Axis

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all planets. These are the objects that orbit a star or star remnant. To be a planet, an object must: must be large enough to be rounded by its own gravity, is not massive enough to cause thermonuclear fusion, and finally, has cleared its region of planetesimals.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Planet
Planeta
Plan??te

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Value type collecting the data on a given set of planetographic coordinates.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Planetographic Coordinate

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:astronomy.planetographic_coordinate to the mso:astronomy.planetographic_coordinate_system the coordinates use.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coordinate System

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An astronomical event in which the sun, moon, and earth are aligned, and the moon at least partially obscures the sun.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Solar Eclipse

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a solar eclipse to a standard descriptor for the kind of eclipse.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Eclipse Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a solar eclipse to the ratio of the apparent size of the moon to the apparent size of the sun during the period in which the sun is most obscured by the moon.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Magnitude

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a solar eclipse to a location where the maximum eclipse can be observed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Location

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a solar eclipse to the time when the maximum eclipse can be observed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Eclipse Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a solar eclipse to the time when the partial eclipse begins. Note that this property is relevant in all cases of solar eclipse. In particular, a total solar eclipse will have both a period of total eclipse and a period of partial eclipse.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Partial Eclipse Begins

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a solar eclipse to the time when the partial eclipse ends. Note that this property is relevant in all cases of solar eclipse. In particular, a total solar eclipse will have both a period of total eclipse and a period of partial eclipse.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Partial Eclipse Ends

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a solar eclipse to the time when the total eclipse begins. Note that this property is relevant only in cases of total solar eclipse. Note too that a total solar eclipse will have both a period of total eclipse and a period of partial eclipse.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Eclipse Begins

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a solar eclipse to the time when the total eclipse ends. Note that this property is relevant only in cases of total solar eclipse. Note too that a total solar eclipse will have both a period of total eclipse and a period of partial eclipse.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Eclipse Ends

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration type containing values for the various kinds of solar eclipses.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Solar Eclipse Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An eclipse in which the sun, moon, and earth are aligned, but the apparent size of the moon is smaller than the apparent size of the sun.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Annular Eclipse

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An eclipse that involves a shift between a total eclipse and an annular eclipse.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hybrid Eclipse

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An eclipse in which the sun, moon, and earth are not completely aligned, and the moon only partially obscures the sun.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Partial Eclipse

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A solar eclipse in which the moon completely obscures the sun, with only the sun's corona visible.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Eclipse

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the categories of stars. Stellar classification is a classification of stars based on their spectral characteristics. Most stars are currently classified using the letters O, B, A, F, G, K and M, where O stars are the hottest and the letter sequence indicates successively cooler stars up to the coolest M class. According to an informal tradition, O stars are "blue", B "blue-white", A stars "white", F stars "yellow-white", G stars "yellow", K stars "orange", and M stars "red." The spectrum letter designation is further enhanced by a numerical addition of 0-9 for tenths of the range between two star classes.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Spectral Type
